# 3) production: average the temperature profile, then re-arm the swap so its
#    accumulator counts only the production interval.  fix ave/chunk must be
#    defined BEFORE fix thermal/conductivity so the profile is sampled before
#    each momentum swap (otherwise LAMMPS warns and the swap slabs are biased).
unfix swap
compute ke all ke/atom
variable temp atom c_ke/(1.5*8.617333e-5)
compute layers all chunk/atom bin/1d z lower 0.05 units reduced
fix prof all ave/chunk 200 500 400000 layers v_temp file profile_${tag}_${nz}.dat
fix prof all ave/chunk 200 500 400000 layers v_temp file profile_tersoff_${nz}.dat
fix prof all ave/chunk 200 500 400000 layers v_temp file profile_tersoff_20.dat
fix swap all thermal/conductivity ${swap} z 20
fix swap all thermal/conductivity 100 z 20
variable t0 equal $(time)
variable t0 equal 130
run 400000
